When `Scrollable` widgets nested and the inner `Scrollable` widget have an `AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics` physics,
the inner widget becomes `setCanDrag(true)` as following code:
https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/a7f5fd5360007518644597c60a1f2169eacccc2b/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/scroll_position_with_single_context.dart#L103-L107
Actually, when `Scrollable` nested, the inner widget should `setCanDrag(false)`, otherwise, when the content size bigger than the screen size it becomes not scrollable.
```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(App());
}

class App extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'SelectableText with AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics',
      localizationsDelegates: [],
      home: HomePage(),
    );
  }
}

class HomePage extends StatelessWidget {
  const HomePage({Key key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: SingleChildScrollView(
        child: SelectableText(
          List.generate(1000, (index) => index.toString()).join(" "),
        scrollPhysics: AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics(),
          // or
//         scrollPhysics: AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics(parent: ClampingScrollPhysics()),
          // or
//         scrollPhysics: ClampingScrollPhysics(parent: AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics()),
          // or
//         scrollPhysics: AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics(parent: BouncingScrollPhysics()),
          // or
//         scrollPhysics: BouncingScrollPhysics(parent: AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics()),
          // or ...
          key: Key('Text'),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
Run the code above and the text becomes not scrollable when set the inner scrollable widget an `AlwaysScrollableScrollPhysics`.

This issue can workaround by set `physics` to the outer scrollable widget.

I am not sure this situation is a bug or should documentation for the developers.

