Nonetheless, the suggested approach in the doc does not solve the original issue.

> I now use a `Stack` and `Positioned` to place the icon instead of `suffixeIcon` or `prefixIcon`, which works fine:

That is nice workaround however `contentPadding: EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 12, 36, 12),` is not proper since the default one varies by state:

https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html

> The padding for the input decoration's container.
> 
> The decoration's container is the area which is filled if [filled](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/filled.html) is true and [border](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/border.html)ed per the border. It's the area adjacent to [icon](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/icon.html) and above the widgets that contain [helperText](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/helperText.html), [errorText](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/errorText.html), and [counterText](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/counterText.html).
> 
> By default the [contentPadding](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html) reflects [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) and the type of the [border](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/border.html).
> 
> If [isCollapsed](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isCollapsed.html) is true then [contentPadding](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html) is [EdgeInsets.zero](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/painting/EdgeInsets/zero-constant.html).
> 
> If isOutline property of [border](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/border.html) is false and if [filled](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/filled.html) is true then [contentPadding](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html) is EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 8, 12, 8) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is true and EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 12, 12, 12) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is false. If isOutline property of [border](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/border.html) is false and if [filled](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/filled.html) is false then [contentPadding](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html) is EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(0, 8, 0, 8) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is true and EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(0, 12, 0, 12) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is false.
> 
> If isOutline property of [border](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/border.html) is true then [contentPadding](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/contentPadding.html) is EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 20, 12, 12) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is true and EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 24, 12, 16) when [isDense](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/InputDecoration/isDense.html) is false.

So instead of `contentPadding: EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(12, 12, 36, 12),` use `suffixIcon: SizedBox.shrink(),`, here is the updated version:

<details><summary>updated code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
