### Steps to reproduce

1. Add a Selection Area
2. Add a ListView with multiple text widgets and `reversed: true` as child
3. Open the keyboard
4. Press and hold on some text to select it => the keyboard will lose focus and gets closed, the word you pressed gets marked
5. extend the selection, and you will see that the selection is buggy until you reach the position on the screen where you started the selection while the keyboard was still open

Remove the reversed and everything will work fine as the ListView content will not move with the keyboard.

For a minimal working example, see the link below. In the example, you can change the reversed flag by a toggle in the AppBar.

### Expected results

The selection should just work as expected after the keyboard has closed. The fact that the selected text is then at a different place on the screen should not change the behavior.

### Actual results

The text is not selected until you reach the original position of the selected text. After you reached that once, everything is working as expected again.

