### Behaviour

How app is behaving running on a local web-server tested on a mobile browser on same network.

`flutter run -d web-server --web-port 8001 --web-hostname 0.0.0.0 -t lib/main.dart`

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/112465804/195792010-e279b531-5d96-4913-a9d4-d7a61dc1d38e.mp4

### Observations

- As @nayanAubie has demoed that **when using custom fonts** web app is **facing issues even with normal textfields** like email as well. **When using no custom fonts** like I have done, there is a very minor gap between cursor and the handle on the normal email field, **but on a toggleable password textfield, cursor and selection handle gap is very huge in non obscured password**.
- I have also noticed **double selection handles** showing up. In the attached video if you can see, it is showing orange selection handle, but it is also sometimes showing primaryColor handle below the orange one. (Orange color must be coming from Brave browser I suppose as on Chrome it is showing blue, when running on Android app Webview handle shows Green color, but behaviour remains the same)
- For password field one more observation I had was that in **non obscure mode** selection handle is still showing up at a position where the character would be in obscured mode. So if I tap between 8th and 9th character, handle would appear at a position where 8th and 9th character would be in obscure mode.

## Triage report

I can reproduce this issue. This seems to happen only with the canvaskit renderer.

